    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Debating Global Warming</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter Kurz letter on December 3 article questions why military planners are preparing for worst case in Iraq while US government is failing to provide leadership on global warming</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An axiom of our military planners is that we must be prepared for the worst (''Global Warming''). If this is appropriate in military matters, how much more so for matters of the viability of earth. The worst case is unfortunately very plausible in the judgment of many scientists; but remedies are also available given the moral and political will.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An axiom of our military planners is that we must be prepared for the worst (''Global Warming''). If this is appropriate in military matters, how much more so for matters of the viability of earth. The worst case is unfortunately very plausible in the judgment of many scientists; but remedies are also available given the moral and political will.</p>
        <p>The failure of our national government to provide needed leadership on this front strikes me as almost astonishingly shortsighted.</p>
        <p>PETER KURZ  Glen Rock, N.J.</p>
      </block>
